ENTRY            F1543   20260115   20260305   20260305       F106
SUBENT        F1543001   20260115   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                 12         39
TITLE      Excitation functions for Sc radioisotopes production
           via (alpha,x) nuclear reactions on natural calcium up
           to 25 MeV
AUTHOR     (L.A.Hasnowo,A.A.Garapatsky,N.E.Villa,M.S.Larkina,
           I.V.Lomov,M.S.Yusubov)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSTPI) School of Nuclear Science and Engineering;
           Research Centrum for Oncotheranostics, Research School
           of Chemistry and Applied Biomedical Sciences
           (3INSINS) National Research and Innovation Agency,
           Yogyakarta, Indonesia
           (4RUSRUS) Department of Pharmaceutical Analysis,
           Siberian State Medical University, Tomsk
REFERENCE  (J,RPC,227,112361,2025)
           #doi:10.1016/j.radphyschem.2024.112361
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4RUSTPI) U-120 Cyclotron
SAMPLE     NatCaCO3 powder (purity: 99.5%) was used as calcium
           target samples. The samples were prepared by
           sedimentation technique and followed by compaction
           wrapped in thin aluminium foil, which strengthens
           mechanically. The thicknesses of the formed CaCO3
           layer were 4.48-11.15 mg/cm2 for the targets. Three
           stacks of samples with different configurations were
           used. The natCu and natTi foils were used as beam
           monitors, and beam energy degraders.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) High-purity Ge gamma-ray detector (Canberra,
           type GC1020) with a multi-channel analyzer was used.
METHOD     (STTA,GSPEC,EDEG)
           (ACTIV) Stacks were irradiated for 1 hour under
           vacuum conditions.
ERR-ANALYS The total uncertainty of the beam energy at each foil
           was estimated using the SRIM software by the
           uncertainties of the primary beam energy (0.3 MeV) and
           target thicknesses (1-2%).
ADD-RES    (COMP) The obtained results were critically compared
           with previous experimental reports and with
           theoretical data obtained by the EMPIRE-3.2.3 code
           and from the TENDL-2021 library.
STATUS     (APRVD) Entry was approved by Dr. L.A. Hasnowo.
HISTORY    (20260115C)
